text:
I was able to add PWA functionality to a React app by hosting the manifest and js bundles on hubfs. After putting the files in the file manager, I created a template that imports the assets and renders the app. Hereâ€™s a snippet of the start of my template where the manifest is loaded:

```&lt;!--
  templateType: "page"
  isAvailableForNewContent: true
--&gt;
<!DOCTYPE html>
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset="utf-8" /&gt;
    &lt;meta name="description" content="Your description" /&gt;
        {{ standard_header_includes }}
    &lt;link rel="manifest" href="<https://www.yourdomain.com/hubfs/pathToProject/manifest.json>" /&gt;```
You also need to include the correct meta tags and icon links for the devices you are targeting in the template.  Check out <https://github.com/onderceylan/pwa-asset-generator> for an easy way to generate those. Once generated, you can just copy and paste them into the head tag of the template.

Lmk if you have any issues
